<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Rangers conceded their first goals of the Scottish Premiership season as Christian Doidge's header held the table toppers to a 2-2 draw on Sunday.</p>

<p>Drey Wright ended the visitors' remarkable seven-match run of clean sheets with the opener, only for striker Alfredo Morelos to fire an equaliser on the stroke of half-time.</p>

<p>Scott Arfield put Rangers back in front from close range after 57 minutes but a mistake by centre-back Connor Goldson allowed forward Doidge to head Hibs level.</p>

<p>Drey Wright finishes a slick team move to put Hibs ahead in the 22nd minute against Rangers</p>

